                                  Alchemy

    Alchemists turn gathered herbs and saved reagents into potions, field
supplies, and profession recipe outputs. The core alchemy room is in the
profession building, 4e, n from Center of Town.

Getting started:
  1. Buy profession tools in the profession building.
  2. Gather herbs with 'gather herbs' or buy/hire workers for materials.
  3. Go to the alchemy room and use 'potions' to see potion names.
  4. Use 'quickcraft <potion>' to brew a potion.

    Each potion has 4 strengths, matching the level requirement to quaff
it. Level 1 potions can be quaffed by anyone. Level 2 potions require
level 20. Level 3 potions require level 45. Level 4 potions require
level 65.

    Level 1 potions can be made by anyone and can raise your skill to 100.
Level 2 potions need Alchemy 60 and can raise your skill to 200. Level 3
potions need Alchemy 100 and can raise your skill to 500. Level 4 potions
need Alchemy 200 and can raise your skill to 1000.

    Alchemy also uses recipe cards. Read a recipe card to see its saved
material requirements, then use 'manufacture card' while carrying the card.
Recipe cards may come from work orders and other profession rewards.

    Weapon oil is one such recipe output. Use 'oil <weapon>' while carrying
crafted weapon oil to give the weapon a modest temporary hit bonus and make
it less likely to break while the oil lasts. Better Alchemy skill improves
the bonus and duration.

Useful commands:
  help potions
  help herbalism
  help workorders
  professions crafting
  professions check potion str1
  quickcraft str1
  manufacture card
